Program: Great Lives
Title: Bill Hamilton
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00qc2hn
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 27 Oct 2017
Matthew Parris presents the biographical series in which his guests choose someone who has inspired their lives. Professor Richard Dawkins explains why he believes Bill Hamilton to have been one of the greatest evolutionary theorists of the 20th century. Dr Mary Bliss offers expert advice.